ENTRY            33226   20260406   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        33226001   20260406   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 14         36
TITLE      Determination of thermal neutron capture cross-section
            of cerium isotopes
AUTHOR     (Samrudhi R.Kanjarpane, P.M.Prajapati, S.Shet, B.Soni,
            D.Bhandari, R.Kumar, R.G.Pizzone, S.V.Suryanarayana)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMNP,2ITYLNS,3INDBDA,3INDTRM,2ITYCAT)
           (3INDIND) ITM SLS Baroda University, Vadodara
           (3INDIND) Homi Bhabha National Institute, Mumbai
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,61,149,2025)
SAMPLE     Natural CeO2 powder (1.8 gm, 1.66 g cerium) was
            pelletised at 5 MPa. The pellet had a height of
            4.3 mm, radius of 6.5 mm, and density of 3.14 g/cm3.
INC-SOURCE (AM-BE) The neutron source having yield of
            4 X 10**7 neutrons/second in 4pi geometry.
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Irradiation: 14 days; counting: 27 hours.
ANALYSIS   A value of 73.8% was adopted for the
            thermal-to-epithermal neutron ratio based on previous
            measurements using cadmium covers.
MONITOR    (79-AU-197(N,G)79-AU-198,,SIG)
DECAY-MON  (79-AU-198-G,2.7D,DG,411.,0.965)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainties are due to
           (ERR-1) Counting statistics of 140Ce, 142Ce
           (ERR-2) Counting statistics of 197Au
           (ERR-3) Detector efficiency of 140Ce, 142Ce
           (ERR-4) Detector efficiency of 197Au
           (ERR-5) Gamma emission probability of 140Ce, 142Ce
           (ERR-6) Gamma emission probability of 197Au
           (ERR-7) Time factor of 140Ce, 142Ce
           (ERR-8) Time factor of 197Au
           (ERR-9) Atomic mass of 140Ce, 142Ce
           (ERR-10) Atomic mass of 197Au
           (ERR-11) Sample mass of 197Au
           (MONIT-ERR) Monitor cross section of 197Au
STATUS     (TABLE,,Samrudhi R.Kanjarpane+,J,EPJ/A,61,149,2025)
            Table 10,12
HISTORY    (20260406C) VT
